---
const _updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of use — Blog" description="The rules for using blog.oriz.in." hideSidebar={true}>
  <header class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Blog</a> / <a href="/legal/">Legal</a> / Terms</p>
    <h1>Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="prose">
    <p>
      By using blog.oriz.in, you agree to these terms. They are short on purpose.
    </p>

    <h2>Use the site lawfully</h2>
    <p>
      Don't try to break the site, scrape it at abusive rates, or use it to
      harass others. Account takeover, copyright infringement, and any
      activity prohibited under Indian law are forbidden.
    </p>

    <h2>Content is provided as-is</h2>
    <p>
      Articles here cover engineering, finance, and books for information and
      convenience only. They are not professional advice. Verify anything
      before relying on it. See the full
      <a href="/legal/disclaimer/">disclaimer</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content</h2>
    <p>
      Public comments on blog posts (via Giscus) are governed by GitHub's
      terms in addition to these. Anything you save locally (bookmarks)
      stays in your browser.
    </p>

    <h2>Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You can delete your account at any time from the
      <a href="https://account.oriz.in/sign-in">account page</a>. We can suspend accounts engaged in
      abuse without notice.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, blog.oriz.in and its operator
      are not liable for any indirect or consequential damages arising from
      use of the site.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of India. Disputes will be settled
      in the courts of Bhubaneswar, Odisha.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); max-width: var(--container-prose, 720px); margin-inline: auto; }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-fg-muted); font-size: 0.8125rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .eyebrow a { color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0; }
  .meta { color: var(--color-fg-soft); font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
  .prose { padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem; color: var(--color-prose); line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.0625rem; max-width: var(--container-prose, 720px); margin-inline: auto; }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 2rem 0 1rem; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
